# 📌 Task Management Backend API

## 🚀 Overview

This project is a **secure RESTful API** built using Node.js and Express.js.
It allows users to register, log in, and manage their personal tasks with proper authentication and authorization.

The system uses:

- **PostgreSQL** → for user data
- **MongoDB** → for task data

---

## 🛠 Tech Stack

- Node.js
- Express.js
- PostgreSQL (pg)
- MongoDB (Mongoose)
- JWT (Authentication)
- bcrypt.js (Password Hashing)
- Joi (Validation)
- dotenv (Environment Variables)

---

## 📂 Folder Structure

```
project/
│── src/
│   ├── config/        # DB connections
│   ├── controller/    # Business logic
│   ├── middleware/    # Auth & error handling
│   ├── models/        # MongoDB schemas
│   ├── routes/        # API routes
│   ├── utils/         # Validation (Joi)
│
│── .env
│── server.js
```

---

## ⚙️ Setup Instructions

### 1️⃣ Clone Repository

```
git clone <your-repo-link>
cd project-folder
```

### 2️⃣ Install Dependencies

```
npm install
```

### 3️⃣ Create `.env` File

```
PORT=5000
JWT_SECRET=your_secret_key

# PostgreSQL (Neon / any cloud)
PG_URI=your_postgres_connection_string

# MongoDB (Atlas)
MONGO_URI=your_mongodb_connection_string
```

---

### 4️⃣ Run Server

```
npm run dev
```

Server will start at:

```
http://localhost:5000
```

---

## 🔐 Authentication

All protected routes require JWT token:

```
Authorization: Bearer <token>
```

---

## 📌 API Endpoints

### 👤 Auth Routes

#### Register User

```
POST /api/auth/register
```

Body:

```json
{
  "email": "test@gmail.com",
  "password": "123456"
}
```

---

#### Login User

```
POST /api/auth/login
```

Response:

```json
{
  "token": "your_jwt_token"
}
```

---

#### Get Profile (Protected)

```
GET /api/auth/me
```

Response:

```json
{
  "id": 1,
  "email": "test@gmail.com"
}
```

---

## 📝 Task Routes (Protected)

#### Create Task

```
POST /api/tasks
```

```json
{
  "title": "Task",
  "description": "Test",
  "dueDate": "2026-04-25",
  "status": "pending"
}
```

---

#### Get All Tasks

```
GET /api/tasks
```

---

#### Get Single Task

```
GET /api/tasks/:id
```

---

#### Update Task

```
PUT /api/tasks/:id
```

---

#### Delete Task

```
DELETE /api/tasks/:id
```

---

## 🔒 Security Features

- Password hashing using bcrypt
- JWT-based authentication
- Protected routes with middleware
- Ownership check (users can only access their own tasks)

---

## ⚠️ Error Handling

Global error handler implemented for:

- 400 → Bad Request
- 401 → Unauthorized
- 403 → Forbidden
- 404 → Not Found
- 500 → Server Error

---

## ✅ Data Validation

- Email format validation
- Password length validation
- Task fields validation (title, dueDate, etc.)

---

## 🧠 Design Decisions

- **PostgreSQL for Users**
  Structured data (email, password) fits relational DB.

- **MongoDB for Tasks**
  Flexible schema for task management.

- **JWT Authentication**
  Stateless and scalable.

- **Modular Structure**
  Clean separation of concerns (routes, controllers, models).

---

## 🧪 Testing

All APIs tested using Postman.

